data.name: Grilled Asparagus and Mushroom Risotto
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy, rich risotto infused with earthy mushrooms and fresh grilled asparagus, perfect for a satisfying vegetarian meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Begin by heating the vegetable broth in a saucepan over low heat, keeping it warm throughout the cooking process.
In a separate large pan, heat the olive oil and 1 tablespoon of butter over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and minced garlic, saut√©ing until the onion is translucent.
Add the Arborio rice to the pan, stirring for about 2 minutes to toast the rice lightly.
Pour in a ladle of warm vegetable broth and stir continuously until the liquid is mostly absorbed.
Continue adding the broth, one ladle at a time, stirring often, until the rice is creamy and al dente (approximately 18-20 minutes).
While the risotto cooks, prepare the asparagus by trimming the ends and grilling them until tender and slightly charred. Slice them into 2-inch pieces.
In the same pan, add the sliced mushrooms and cook until golden brown. Season with salt and pepper.
Once the risotto is cooked, stir in the mushrooms, grilled asparagus, remaining butter, and Parmesan cheese. Mix well until creamy. Adjust seasoning as needed.
Serve the risotto hot, garnished with fresh parsley and extra Parmesan if desired.
